tantine and the Captive Christians of Persia presents an evocative and evolving portrait of the first Christian emperor, uncovering how Syriac Christians manipulated the image of their western Christian counterparts to fashion their own political and religious identities during this century of radical change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aRELIGION / Ancient.2bisacsh  a4th century mesopotamia.  abyzantine.  achristian converts.  achristian roman empire.  aconstantine.  aconversion to christianity.  aeastern christians.  aecclesiastical histories.  afirst christian emperor.  ahagiography.  ahistory of constantine.  ahistory of persia.  amiddle eastern christianity.  apersecution of christians in persia.  apersia.  aroman empire.  asasanian empire.  asyriac christianity.  asyriac christians.  azoroastrian sasanian empire.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106675470 cprintz978052028960440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052096420440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520964204423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520964204/original  a978-3-11-066754-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY